<p>8/18/2016</p><p><br>&nbsp;</p><p>​CHARLESTON, W.Va. - DMV Commissioner Pat Reed is pleased to announce that the long-awaited move of the current DMV Regional Office in Bridgeport, to the brand new facility in downtown Clarksburg, will begin August 25th. The current office, located at 105 Platinum Drive, will be closed August 25th and 26th so that staff can move into the new office and be ready for business at 8:30 a.m. on Monday, August 29th. The new location will&nbsp;be at 153 West Main Street in Clarksburg. Customers needing DMV services&nbsp;on Thursday and Friday, August 25th and 26th&nbsp;may visit another local DMV Regional Office. Other offices in the area are found in Fairmont, Elkins, Flatwoods, Morgantown and Parkersburg.<br>&nbsp;</p><p>For more information, please contact the WV DMV at 1-800-642-9066, or visit the DMV website at <a href="http://dmv.wv.gov/">dmv.wv.gov</a>.</p><h2><strong>Contact:</strong></h2><p>&nbsp;<br>1-800-642-9066</p>